<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>While there will be no star-studded red carpet at the Emmy Awards this year, Jennifer Aniston is getting ready for TV's biggest day from home.</p>

<p>The 51-year-old actress shared a new snap from her home on Instagram, where she gave fans a glimpse of her Emmy prep.</p>

<p>The Friends star even made a face mask joke as TV's best and brightest prepare for a major awards show amid the COVID-19 pandemic. </p>

<p>Emmy prep: While there will be no star-studded red carpet at the Emmy Awards this year, Jennifer Aniston is getting ready for TV's biggest day from home</p>

<p>Aniston was seen blowing a kiss while wearing grey pajamas while holding a glass of champagne and wearing a masque treatment on her face.</p>

<p>'Emmys prep... in my other mask,' she joked, while including a face mask emoji and two champagne glass emoji.</p>

<p>'Congratulations to the nominees and all of the amazing performances we’ve seen this year' she concluded with a heart emoji and clapping emojis.</p>

<p>Jen's look: Aniston was seen blowing a kiss while wearing grey pajamas while holding a glass of champagne and wearing a masque treatment on her face</p>

<p>Aniston is one of the nominees herself this year, up for Lead Actress in a Drama series for her work in Apple TV Plus' The Morning Show.</p>

<p>She is nominated alongside The Crown's Olivia Colman, Killing Eve's Jodie Comer, Ozark's Laura Linney, Killing Eve's Sandra Oh and Euphoria's Zendaya.  </p>

<p>First Emmy: If Aniston wins tonight, it will mark her second Emmy win, following her 2002 win for Outstanding Lead Actress in a Comedy Series for Friends</p>

<p>Aniston also earned four more Emmy nominations for her time on Friends, plus Outstanding Guest Actress in a Comedy Series for her stint on 30 Rock in 2009.</p>

<p>The Morning Show marks Aniston's first return to TV in a starring role, playing Alex Levy in The Morning Show, inspired by Brian Stelter's book Top of the Morning: Inside the Cutthroat World of Morning TV.</p>

<p>Alex Levy is an anchor on a hit morning show in New York, whose partner gets fired after a sexual misconduct scandal as she fights to keep her job from emerging reporter Bradley Jackson (Reese Witherspoon).</p>

<p>Emmy nomination: Aniston also earned four more Emmy nominations for her time on Friends, plus Outstanding Guest Actress in a Comedy Series for her stint on 30 Rock in 2009</p>

<p>Aniston is coming off a highly-publicized virtual reunion with ex Brad Pitt at a table read of the Fast Times at Ridgemont High script last week.</p>

<p>She is also attached to star in Hail Mary, playing Denise White, a former Miss USA contestant becomes a successful sports manager.</p>

<p>She is also slated to reunite with all of her Friends co-stars in a Friends reunion special for HBO Max, though it remains to be seen when it will start production. </p>

